<title>JAPAN: Japan Mar platinum imports fall 19.7 pct yr/yr.</title>
<headline>Japan Mar platinum imports fall 19.7 pct yr/yr.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-04-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>Japan's platinum imports in March fell 19.7 percent from a year earlier to 5.49 tonnes, Finance Ministry data released on Monday showed.</p>
<p>The figures were as follows (in tonnes):</p>
<p>		     Mar 97     Feb 97     Mar 96</p>
<p> Total	     5.49	 5.20	 6.84</p>
<p>Major suppliers:</p>
<p> South Africa    3.12	 4.07	 3.20</p>
<p> Russia	    0.40	  nil	 2.22</p>
<p>Cumulative imports in the first three months of 1997 totalled 17.79 tonnes, down from 17.96 tonnes in the same period a year earlier.</p>
<p>-- Tokyo Commodities Desk +81-3-3432-7391</p>
</text>
